---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Disconnect an integration — 1404 Mission Control"
  description="Remove QuickBooks Online, Microsoft 365, or Google Workspace from your Mission Control instance."
>
  <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 pt-40 pb-24">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-text-primary mb-4">Disconnect an integration</h1>
    <p class="text-text-muted text-lg mb-12">
      To disconnect an integration from your Mission Control instance, follow these steps.
      You can also revoke access directly from the provider at any time.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 bg-bg-surface">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-text-primary mb-3">Disconnect from Mission Control</h2>
        <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-text-secondary text-sm">
          <li>Log in to <code class="text-copper">https://{your-company}.mc.1404.io</code></li>
          <li>Click <strong>Integrations</strong> in the left sidebar</li>
          <li>Find the integration you want to disconnect</li>
          <li>Click <strong>Disconnect</strong> on that card</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mt-4">
          When you disconnect, Mission Control deletes the OAuth tokens from its vault
          and stops accessing the integration immediately.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 bg-bg-surface">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-text-primary mb-3">Revoke access at the provider</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mb-3">
          You can also revoke Mission Control's access directly from each provider.
          This is the most thorough option — it tells the provider to invalidate our tokens
          even if we haven't asked yet.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-text-secondary text-sm">
          <li>
            <strong>QuickBooks Online:</strong>
            <a href="https://app.qbo.intuit.com/app/settings/connectedapps"
               class="text-copper hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              Connected Apps page
            </a> → find "1404 Mission Control" → Disconnect
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Microsoft 365:</strong>
            <a href="https://myapps.microsoft.com"
               class="text-copper hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              My Apps
            </a> → find "1404 Mission Control" → Remove
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Workspace:</strong>
            <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions"
               class="text-copper hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              Third-party apps
            </a> → find "1404 Mission Control" → Remove access
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 bg-bg-surface">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-text-primary mb-2">Full account deletion</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">
          To delete your entire Mission Control account and all associated data, email
          <a href="mailto:holden@1404.io" class="text-copper hover:underline">holden@1404.io</a>.
          We permanently delete all customer data within 60 days of termination. See our
          <a href="/privacy" class="text-copper hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a> for details.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
